President Biden delivered a speech at the groundbreaking ceremony for Intel's new $20 billion campus in New Albany, Ohio. He highlighted the importance of manufacturing semiconductors in America and the role they play in everyday life, from smartphones to cars to national security. He emphasized that the United States needs to lead in producing advanced chips and that the CHIPS and Science Act, which he signed into law, will help boost research and development investment and attract private investment. The President also mentioned the importance of infrastructure investment, the need to create good-paying union jobs, and the potential for economic and national security through domestic chip production.